        public LikePatternSyntax getLikeSyntax()
        Returns:
        the LikePatternSyntax of the search string used to do a LIKE-search, null for no LIKE-search. Shall be null if operator is neither null nor StringSearchOperator.LIKE.

      • setLikeSyntax

      • getOperator

        public StringSearchOperator getOperator()
        Returns:
        operator the StringSearchOperator used to search. If null a "magic auto mode" is used where StringSearchOperator.LIKE is used in case the search string contains wildcards and StringSearchOperator.EQ is used otherwise.
